ShellCheck is a static analysis tool for shell scripts.
It is designed to identify and suggest corrections for common bugs and stylistic issues
in shell scripts written for various Unix shells like bash, sh, ksh, and zsh.
ShellCheck helps improve the quality and robustness of shell scripts by providing insights
into potential errors, bad practices, and portability issues.

Installing ShellCheck on Ubuntu/Debian:

	sudo apt install shellcheck
	
Running ShellCheck:

	shellcheck myscript.sh
	
Integrating ShellCheck with Editors:

Many text editors and IDEs have plugins to integrate ShellCheck, providing real-time feedback as you write your scripts. Popular options include:

    Visual Studio Code: ShellCheck extension
